      public boolean extractSupply​(int amount)
      Method used for extracting a specific amount of supplies from a given source.
      Parameters:
      amount - indicates how many units of supplies it should extract.
      Returns:
      whether or not the extraction was possible. The only case when it returns false is when the requested amount is bigger than the current amount.
